For each significant architectural decision in the design, produce a
trade-off analysis. Focus on decisions that are non-obvious or where
a reasonable engineer might choose differently.

Rules:
- optimises_characteristics and sacrifices_characteristics must each
  contain at least one characteristic name from the characteristics
  list above. Do not invent new characteristic names.
- acceptable_because must be specific to this system's context —
  not a generic justification.
- context_dependency must describe the condition under which this
  trade-off recommendation inverts. If it never inverts, say so
  and explain why.
- confidence must be "high", "medium", or "low" with a reason.

Return a JSON object with exactly this structure. No markdown, no preamble:
{
  "decisions": [
    {
      "decision_id": "TD-001",
      "decision": "string — the architectural choice made",
      "options_considered": [
        {
          "option": "string — the alternative",
          "rejected_because": "string — specific reason for rejection"
        }
      ],
      "optimises_characteristics": ["string — characteristic names"],
      "sacrifices_characteristics": ["string — characteristic names"],
      "acceptable_because": "string — why this sacrifice is acceptable
                              in this system's specific context",
      "context_dependency": "string — condition that would invert this
                              recommendation",
      "recommendation": "string — the decision restated as a directive",
      "confidence": "high | medium | low",
      "confidence_reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "dominant_tension": "string — the single most important trade-off
